  journal  = "Nat. Genet.",
  volume   =  51,
  number   =  3,
  pages    = "481--493",
  abstract = "Reduced lung function predicts mortality and is key to the
              diagnosis of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). In a
              genome-wide association study in 400,102 individuals of European
              ancestry, we define 279 lung function signals, 139 of which are
              new. In combination, these variants strongly predict COPD in
